\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Wanted
\series default
: the 
\series bold
\color blue
distribution of a transformed variable 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Y=g(X)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Why? We often need to 
\series bold
\color blue
transform the data
\series default
\color inherit
.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Bayes: we often need to transform parameters.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

